    <note>Chen(1) Congyi [93] Su(1) Shen's [7341] father-in-law, Su(1) Song's [8116] maternal grandfather. Lu(1) Shengqing's [1323] father-in-law, Chen(1) Congyi(2) [3086], was probably a lineage cousin. The disparity in periods in office is not unusual. Congyi [93] received his jinshi in 989 and his cousin Congzhi [3085] received his in 1012. Congyi's [93] son-in-law Su(1) Jie [3753], who received the jinshi in 1034, is probably a son or nephew of Su(1) Guohua [3764], who received the jinshi in 989, and a brother or cousin of both Guohua's son Su(1) Shou [3769], who received the jinshi in 1024 and Hu(1) Ze's [829] son-in-law, Su(1) Fan [7339]. Fujian TZ, 147.3b, 8b; XCB, 98.1a; SS, 300.26a; Su Song, WJ, 62.5b. CBD, 3, 2615-6.</note>
